# Neural Retail PostgreeSQL Queries  

This project contains SQL queries and views created on a retail dataset (`retail_data` table).  
The goal was to analyze sales, customers, products, and revenue trends.

## 📊 Queries Implemented
1. **Total Revenue** – SUM of all sales
2. **Total Customers** – Count of distinct customers
3. **Top 10 Customers** – Highest revenue contributors
4. **Top 10 Products** – Most sold products
5. **Revenue by Country** – Country-wise revenue distribution
6. **Daily Sales Trend** – Sales trend over time

## 🗂️ SQL Views
7. **Top Customers View** – Reusable view for customer revenue
8. **Top Products View** – Reusable view for product sales
9. **Country Revenue View** – Reusable view for country-wise revenue
10. **Daily Sales Trend View** – Reusable view for daily sales

# Queries 
-- ===========================
-- Retail SQL Analysis Script
-- ===========================

-- 1. Total Revenue
SELECT SUM(totalprice) AS total_revenue
FROM retail_data;

-- 2. Total Customers
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Customerid) AS total_customers
FROM retail_data;

-- 3. Top 10 Customers
SELECT Customerid, SUM(totalPrice) AS revenue
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY Customerid
ORDER BY revenue DESC
LIMIT 10;

-- 4. Top 10 Products
SELECT description, SUM(quantity) AS total_quantity
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY description
ORDER BY total_quantity DESC
LIMIT 10;

-- 5. Revenue by Country
SELECT Country, SUM(totalprice) AS revenue
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY Country
ORDER BY revenue DESC;

-- 6. Daily Sales Trend
SELECT DATE(invoicedate) AS sales_date, SUM(totalprice) AS daily_sales
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY sales_date
ORDER BY sales_date;

-- ===========================
-- SQL Views for Reusability
-- ===========================

-- 7. Top Customers View
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW top_customers_view AS
SELECT customerid, SUM(totalprice) AS revenue
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY customerid
ORDER BY revenue DESC;
SELECT * FROM top_customers_view LIMIT 10;

-- 8. Top Products View
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW top_products_view AS
SELECT description, SUM(quantity) AS total_quantity
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY description
ORDER BY total_quantity DESC;
SELECT * FROM top_products_view LIMIT 10;

-- 9. Country Revenue View
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW country_revenue_view AS
SELECT country, SUM(totalprice) AS revenue
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY country
ORDER BY revenue DESC;
SELECT * FROM country_revenue_view LIMIT 10;

-- 10. Daily Sales Trend View
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW daily_sales_view AS
SELECT DATE(invoicedate) AS sales_date, SUM(totalprice) AS daily_sales
FROM retail_data
GROUP BY sales_date
ORDER BY sales_date;
SELECT * FROM daily_sales_view LIMIT 10;
